INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (870,'199600202004','img;a) The symmetries are ;;(i)	rotation about the centre of the square by $$90^{\\circ}$$;;(ii)	rotation about the centre of the square by $$180^{\\circ}$$;;(iii)	rotation about the centre of the square by $$270^{\\circ}$$;;clockwise and anticlockwise.;;b-i) AB = BC because ABCD is a square.;;BR = BC because BCSR is a rhombus;;AB = BR;;b-ii) since $$\\Delta ABR$$ is isosceles because AB = BR, therefore,;;$$A \\hat RB = \\frac{180^{\\circ}- (90-56)^{\\circ}}{2} = \\frac{144^{\\circ}}{2} = 72^{\\circ}$$ ;;b-iii) since BR is mapped on CT after a $$90^{\\circ}$$ rotation in the clockwise direction about the centre of the square, it means that BR is perpendicular to CT. But BR \\parallel CS, therefore CS is perpendicular to CT. Hence $$\\angle SCT=90^{\\circ}$$');
