INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (1118,'200300202007','a) Surface area ;;$$=\\frac{2 \\pi r^2}{2}+\\frac{1}{2}(2 \\pi rh)+(18 \\times 18 + \\frac{1}{2}(\\pi r^2))+ \\frac{\\pi r^2 }{2}$$;;$$=\\frac{2\\pi(81)}{2}+\\pi(9 \\times 18)+(18 \\times 18 + \\frac{1}{2}(81\\pi))+\\frac{81 \\pi}{2}$$;;$$=81\\pi + 162\\pi + 324 + \\frac{81\\pi}{2}+\\frac{81\\pi}{2}$$;;$$=324\\pi+324$$;;$$\\approx 1342 cm^2 $$;;b) Volume of water;;$$= \\frac{1}{2}[\\frac{2}{3}\\pi r^{3} + \\pi r^2 h]$$;;$$= \\frac{1}{2}[\\frac{2}{3}\\pi (9)^{3} + \\pi (81) (18)]$$;;$$=\\frac{1}{2}(486 \\pi + 1458 \\pi)$$;;$$=972 \\pi cm^{3} $$ (shown);;c) Let the depth of water be x cm.;;$$972 \\pi = \\frac{2}{3}(9)^{3} +\\pi(9)^2 (x-9)$$;;$$972 \\pi = 486 \\pi + 81 \\pi(x-9)$$;;$$486 \\pi = 81 \\pi(x-9)$$;;$$x-9=\\frac{486\\pi}{81\\pi}=6$$;;x = 9 + 6 = 15 cm;;d) $$\\pi(9)^2 h=972\\pi$$;;81h = 972;;h = 12 cm');
