INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (1155,'200400204008','a) Radius of the third circle;;$$=\\frac{1}{2}$$(radius of the smallest circle + radius of the largest circle);;$$=\\frac{1}{2}(2x+2y)$$;;= (x + y) cm;;b-i) Area of the region that is colored yellow ;;$$=\\pi(x+y)^2 -\\pi(2x)^2 $$;;$$=\\pi(x^2 +2xy+y^2)-4\\pi x^2 $$;;$$=\\pi(y^2 +2xy-3x^2) cm^2 $$;;b-ii) Area of the region that is colored green;;$$=\\pi(2y)^2 -\\pi(x+y)^2 $$;;$$=4\\pi y^2 -\\pi(x^2 +2xy+y^2)$$;;$$=\\pi(3y^2 -2xy-x^2) cm^2 $$;;c) Area of the green region = $$2 \\times Area.of.the.yellow.region$$;;$$\\pi(3y^2 -2xy-x^2 )=2\\pi(y^2 +2xy-3x^2)$$;;$$3y^2 -2xy-x^2 =2y^2 +4xy-6x^2 $$;;$$y^2 -6xy+5x^2 =0$$ (shown);;d-i) $$y^2 -6xy+5x^2 =(y-5x)(y-x)$$;;d-ii) $$y^2 -6xy+5x^2 =0$$;;(y - 5x)(y - x) = 0;;$$\\Rightarrow$$ y = 5x or y = x (rejected since y > x);;e) Fraction of the design that is colored yellow;;$$=\\frac{\\pi(y^2 +2xy-3x^2)}{\\pi(2y)^2}$$;;$$=\\frac{(5x)^2 +2x(5x)-3x^2}{(10x)^2}$$;;$$=\\frac{32x^2}{100x^2}$$;;$$=\\frac{8}{25}$$');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (1156,'200400204009','a) $$25^2 -24^2 =(25-24)(25+24)= 1 \\times 49=49=7^2 $$;;$$\\Rightarrow$$ 7, 24 and 25 form a Pythagorean Triple;;b-i) $$41^2 -40^2 =(41-40)(41+40)=1 \\times 81 = 81 = 9^2 $$;;$$\\Rightarrow$$ 9, 40 and 41 form a Pythagorean Triple;;b-ii) $$11^2 =121=(61-60)(61+60)=61^2 -60^2 $$;;$$\\Rightarrow$$ 11, 60 and 61 form a Pythagorean Triple;;c-i) $$(n+1)^2 -n^2 =(n+1-n)(n+1+n)=(1)(2n+1)=2n+1$$;;c-ii) $$2n+1=101^2 $$;;2n = 10200;;n = 5100;;$$\\Rightarrow$$ The Pythagorean Triple is 101, 5100 and 5101;;d-i) $$37^2 -35^2 =(37-35)(37+35)=(2)(72)=144=12^2 $$;;$$65^2 -63^2 =(65-63)(65+63)=(2)(128)=256=16^2 $$;;d-ii) $$(4n^2 +1)^2 -(4n^2 -1)^2 $$;;$$=(4n^2 +1-4n^2 +1)(4n^2 +1+4n^2 -1)$$;;$$=(2)(8n^2)$$;;$$=16n^2 $$;;$$=(4n)^2 $$;;d-iii) 4n = 400;;n = 100;;$$4n^2 +1=4(100)^2 +1=40001$$;;$$4n^2 -1=4(100)^2 -1=39999$$;;$$\\Rightarrow$$ The Pythagorean Triple is 400, 39999 and 40001');
